{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":439,"text":"This is the Bop."}]},{"cues":[{"time":3014,"text":"The Bop is a type of social dance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":9109,"text":"Dance is a language,"},{"time":10773,"text":"and social dance is an expression\nthat emerges from a community."},{"time":15238,"text":"A social dance isn't choreographed\nby any one person."},{"time":18607,"text":"It can't be traced to any one moment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21196,"text":"Each dance has steps\nthat everyone can agree on,"},{"time":24227,"text":"but it's about the individual\nand their creative identity."},{"time":29772,"text":"Because of that,"},{"time":30951,"text":"social dances bubble up,"},{"time":32367,"text":"they change"},{"time":33558,"text":"and they spread like wildfire."}]},{"cues":[{"time":36962,"text":"They are as old as our remembered history."},{"time":41492,"text":"In African-American social dances,"},{"time":43757,"text":"we see over 200 years"},{"time":45529,"text":"of how African and African-American\ntraditions influenced our history."},{"time":52329,"text":"The present always contains the past."},{"time":55388,"text":"And the past shapes who we are"},{"time":57901,"text":"and who we will be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":59517,"text":"(Clapping)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":63304,"text":"The Juba dance was born\nfrom enslaved Africans' experience"},{"time":66475,"text":"on the plantation."},{"time":68312,"text":"Brought to the Americas,"},{"time":69521,"text":"stripped of a common spoken language,"},{"time":71780,"text":"this dance was a way for enslaved Africans\nto remember where they're from."},{"time":76076,"text":"It may have looked something like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":84556,"text":"Slapping thighs,"},{"time":85747,"text":"shuffling feet"},{"time":87005,"text":"and patting hands:"},{"time":88829,"text":"this was how they got around\nthe slave owners' ban on drumming,"},{"time":92974,"text":"improvising complex rhythms"},{"time":95101,"text":"just like ancestors did\nwith drums in Haiti"},{"time":98000,"text":"or in the Yoruba communities\nof West Africa."},{"time":104804,"text":"It was about keeping\ncultural traditions alive"},{"time":107945,"text":"and retaining a sense of inner freedom"},{"time":110302,"text":"under captivity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":113555,"text":"It was the same subversive spirit\nthat created this dance:"},{"time":118191,"text":"the Cakewalk,"},{"time":119385,"text":"a dance that parodied the mannerisms\nof Southern high society --"},{"time":123185,"text":"a way for the enslaved\nto throw shade at the masters."},{"time":126849,"text":"The crazy thing about this dance"},{"time":128824,"text":"is that the Cakewalk\nwas performed for the masters,"},{"time":131785,"text":"who never suspected\nthey were being made fun of."}]},{"cues":[{"time":137069,"text":"Now you might recognize this one."},{"time":139805,"text":"1920s --"},{"time":140999,"text":"the Charleston."},{"time":145715,"text":"The Charleston was all about\nimprovisation and musicality,"},{"time":149490,"text":"making its way into Lindy Hop,"},{"time":151529,"text":"swing dancing"},{"time":152713,"text":"and even the Kid n Play,"},{"time":153974,"text":"originally called the Funky Charleston."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161088,"text":"Started by a tight-knit Black community\nnear Charleston, South Carolina,"},{"time":165246,"text":"the Charleston permeated dance halls"},{"time":167262,"text":"where young women suddenly had\nthe freedom to kick their heels"},{"time":170440,"text":"and move their legs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":177273,"text":"Now, social dance is about\ncommunity and connection;"},{"time":180955,"text":"if you knew the steps,"},{"time":182333,"text":"it meant you belonged to a group."},{"time":184291,"text":"But what if it becomes a worldwide craze?"},{"time":187257,"text":"Enter the Twist."},{"time":188949,"text":"It's no surprise that the Twist\ncan be traced back to the 19th century,"},{"time":193280,"text":"brought to America from the Congo"},{"time":195201,"text":"during slavery."},{"time":196872,"text":"But in the late '50s,"},{"time":198109,"text":"right before the Civil Rights Movement,"},{"time":200207,"text":"the Twist is popularized\nby Chubby Checker and Dick Clark."},{"time":203962,"text":"Suddenly, everybody's doing the Twist:"},{"time":206557,"text":"white teenagers,"},{"time":207774,"text":"kids in Latin America,"},{"time":209385,"text":"making its way into songs and movies."},{"time":212116,"text":"Through social dance,"},{"time":213327,"text":"the boundaries between groups\nbecome blurred."}]},{"cues":[{"time":219196,"text":"The story continues in the 1980s and '90s."},{"time":222866,"text":"Along with the emergence of hip-hop,"},{"time":225126,"text":"African-American social dance\ntook on even more visibility,"},{"time":229092,"text":"borrowing from its long past,"},{"time":231342,"text":"shaping culture and being shaped by it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":242364,"text":"Today, these dances continue\nto evolve, grow and spread."}]},{"cues":[{"time":248020,"text":"Why do we dance?"},{"time":249559,"text":"To move,"},{"time":250752,"text":"to let loose,"},{"time":251965,"text":"to express."},{"time":253364,"text":"Why do we dance together?"},{"time":255200,"text":"To heal,"},{"time":256383,"text":"to remember,"},{"time":257558,"text":"to say: \"We speak a common language."},{"time":260080,"text":"We exist"},{"time":261255,"text":"and we are free.\""}]}]}